        "title": "feat: add issue build override",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add `/clawsweeper build override` parsing and override metadata for issue implementation jobs\n- classify issue implementation blockers as soft or hard so overrides either attempt one bounded PR or produce a safe non-code handoff\n- update refusal messaging, operations docs, and focused parser/intake/router tests\n- hard override jobs now validate as non-code handoffs by blocking `fix`, `raise_pr`, `close`, and `merge`; existing issue implementation jobs are rewritten when an override is requested\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm run build`\n- `pnpm run build:repair`\n- `pnpm exec node --test test/repair/comment-router-core.test.ts test/repair/issue-implementation-intake.test.ts`\n- `pnpm run check`\n\n## Override proof\n\nLocal live proof command after `build:repair` exercised the soft/hard override paths and hard job frontmatter:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"soft\": {\n    \"status\": \"override_queued_for_repair\",\n    \"shouldRepair\": true,\n    \"blockerClass\": \"soft\",\n    \"operatorOverride\": true\n  },\n  \"hard\": {\n    \"status\": \"override_handoff\",\n    \"shouldRepair\": true,\n    \"blockerClass\": \"hard\",\n    \"operatorOverride\": true\n  },\n  \"hardJob\": {\n    \"validateErrors\": [],\n    \"allowedActions\": [\"comment\", \"label\"],\n    \"blockedActions\": [\"fix\", \"raise_pr\", \"close\", \"merge\"],\n    \"allowFixPr\": false,\n    \"containsFixArtifactInstruction\": false,\n    \"containsHandoffInstruction\": true\n  }\n}\n```\n\nFixes https://github.com/openclaw/clawsweeper/issues/200",
